 \n    \n  \n\n\nOn the other hand, we lack validation on most endpoints in general, so...", "url": "https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/pull/7097#discussion_r442657932", "createdAt": "2020-06-19T06:38:02Z", "author": {"login": "vmuzikar"}, "path": "services/src/main/java/org/keycloak/services/resources/admin/RoleContainerResource.java", "diffHunk": "@@ -148,6 +151,38 @@ public Response createRole(final RoleRepresentation rep) {\n                 adminEvent.resource(ResourceType.REALM_ROLE);\n             }\n \n+            // Handling of nested composite roles for KEYCLOAK-12754\n+            if (rep.isComposite() && rep.getComposites() != null) {\n+                RoleRepresentation.Composites composites = rep.getComposites();\n+\n+                Set<String> compositeRealmRoles = composites.getRealm();\n+                if (compositeRealmRoles != null && !compositeRealmRoles.isEmpty()) {\n+                    Set<RoleModel> realmRoles = compositeRealmRoles.stream()\n+                            .map(realm::getRole)\n+                            .filter(Objects::nonNull)", "state": "SUBMITTED", "replyTo": null, "originalCommit": {"oid": "6f2ca347e164ecd141eac633ac4577b5768c9d01"}, "originalPosition": 30}]}}, {"__typename": "HeadRefForcePushedEvent", "beforeCommit": {"oid": "6f2ca347e164ecd141eac633ac4577b5768c9d01", "author": {"user": {"login": "thomasdarimont", "name": "Thomas Darimont"}}, "url": "https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/commit/6f2ca347e164ecd141eac633ac4577b5768c9d01", "committedDate": "2020-05-23T10:49:28Z", "message": "KEYCLOAK-12754 Honor nested composite roles when creating roles via REST API"}, "afterCommit": {"oid": "1c41b2a982695fe6ce8a082bb4a49964f13ee29a", "author": {"user": {"login": "thomasdarimont", "name": "Thomas Darimont"}}, "url": "https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/commit/1c41b2a982695fe6ce8a082bb4a49964f13ee29a", "committedDate": "2020-10-20T20:56:26Z", "message": "KEYCLOAK-12754 Validate composite roles when creating roles via 